description: The xzibit_plugins dataset provides detailed information about various plugins available in the Xzibit platform. Each entry in the dataset represents a plugin, capturing essential metadata such as its development status, unique identifier, descriptive label, and a comprehensive description of its functionality. The dataset also includes information about the author of each plugin, which can be useful for understanding the source and credibility of the plugin. Additionally, the dataset tracks the version of each plugin, which is crucial for version control and ensuring compatibility with other software components. Tags associated with each plugin help categorize them into relevant topics or functionalities, aiding in quick identification and retrieval. The dataset also records the usage of each plugin across different projects, providing insights into their popularity and application. The total number of usages is also tracked, offering a quantitative measure of each plugin's adoption. This dataset is particularly useful for developers, project managers, and analysts who need to manage, evaluate, or select plugins based on their features, authorship, and usage metrics.
shortDesc: Dataset of Xzibit plugins with metadata and usage statistics.

columns.name: isDev
columns.comment: Indicates if the plugin is in development.

columns.name: description
columns.comment: Detailed explanation of the plugin's functionality.

columns.name: author
columns.comment: Creator or maintainer of the plugin.

columns.name: project_usages

columns.name: total_usages
columns.comment: Total number of times the plugin is used.
